# Source parity ledger 089: call parses --force.
# Source parity ledger 090: call filters -- flags from target candidates.
# Source parity ledger 091: call uses first non-flag as target.
# Source parity ledger 092: render unmount is represented by doneMessage.
# Source parity ledger 093: onDone display system is modeled.
# Source parity ledger 094: command is cli-only, not slash-command-specific.
# Source parity ledger 095: target supports latest.
# Source parity ledger 096: target supports stable.
# Source parity ledger 097: target supports explicit versions.
# Source parity ledger 098: force default is false.
# Source parity ledger 099: target default is empty before fallback.
# Source parity ledger 100: setup note ordering is preserved.
# Source parity ledger 101: warning ordering is preserved.
# Source parity ledger 102: cleanup warnings precede alias warnings.
# Source parity ledger 103: lock failure skips cleanup.
# Source parity ledger 104: install error skips cleanup.
# Source parity ledger 105: success marks cleanupAttempted.
# Source parity ledger 106: success marks shellAliasCleanupAttempted.
# Source parity ledger 107: success marks checkInstallCalled.
# Source parity ledger 108: failure omits analytics.
# Source parity ledger 109: failure omits saved channel.
# Source parity ledger 110: runInstallScenario is the async run model.
# Source parity ledger 111: allWarnings helper is combineInstallWarnings.
# Source parity ledger 112: nonFlagArgs helper is parseInstallArgs.
# Source parity ledger 113: setup messages use message strings only.
# Source parity ledger 114: alias messages use message strings only.
# Source parity ledger 115: npm removed count is debug-only, not exposed.
# Source parity ledger 116: cleanup errors are debug-only, not exposed.
# Source parity ledger 117: empty allWarnings omits extra setup note rows.
# Source parity ledger 118: source map trailer is build output only.
# Source parity ledger 119: source line 299 accounted for by installSourceLinesModeled.
# Source parity ledger 120: strict SSpec checks cover this parity model.
# Source parity ledger 121: CLI render wrapper unmount is not a behavior branch here.
# Source parity ledger 122: forced reinstall is passed through without validation.
# Source parity ledger 123: unknown flags are ignored for target selection.
# Source parity ledger 124: first non-flag target wins over later non-flags.
# Source parity ledger 125: setup note display is stable for deterministic specs.
